### TITLE ###
LambdaInheritsEnclosingNarrowing
### DESCRIPTION ###
A lambda defined under a narrowed enclosing scope inherits the
narrowed type for captured variables. (Closure-rule caveat noted
in synthLambda doc - future Pyright-style reassignment-after-
definition tracking will tighten this.)
### INPUT ###
fn f(x: int?):
    if x != null:
        cb = fn():
            y = x
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  x @ 2:8 -> int?
  cb @ 3:9 -> <no-type>
  y @ 4:13 -> <no-type>
  x @ 4:17 -> int

# Symbol types
  cb (local): dynamic
  f (fn): <no-type>
  x (param): int?
  y (local): int

# Diagnostics
  (none)
### TITLE ###
LambdaBodyNarrowingDoesNotLeakOut
### DESCRIPTION ###
Narrowings inside the lambda body shouldn't leak back to the
enclosing scope (tc.frame is restored after the lambda walk).
### INPUT ###
fn f(x: int?):
    cb = fn():
        if x != null:
            a = x
    z = x
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  cb @ 2:5 -> <no-type>
  x @ 3:12 -> int?
  a @ 4:13 -> <no-type>
  x @ 4:17 -> int
  z @ 5:5 -> <no-type>
  x @ 5:9 -> int?

# Symbol types
  a (local): int
  cb (local): dynamic
  f (fn): <no-type>
  x (param): int?
  z (local): int?

# Diagnostics
  (none)
